The Road Ahead
We have built a strong foundation, but a world-class platform needs more features before it's ready for high-end clients. Here is a roadmap of what we can build next to turn this into a fully functional booking engine:

1. The User Experience (Frontend Focus)




Auth Pages: We need the visual Login and Registration screens so users can actually sign in to those accounts we created on the backend.

2. The Engine (Backend Focus)

The Booking Controller: We have the Booking model, but we need the logic to actually process a reservation, check for conflicting dates, and save it to the database.

Middleware Lockdown: We need to activate the "bouncer" we talked about earlier—ensuring that only authenticated users can make a booking, and only Admins can add new properties.

Payments integration: Eventually, we will need to integrate Stripe so users can securely pay for their luxury stays.

Which piece of the puzzle would you like to tackle next? We can stay visual and build the Property Details Page, or we can dive back into the engine and lock down the Authentication Middleware.

The Authentication Phase
The Auth Context: We need to create a secure vault in React to store the user's details and their JWT token after they log in, so every page knows they are authenticated.

The Login & Register Pages: We need to build the sleek, glassmorphic forms where users can type in their credentials and create an account.

The Token Handshake: We need to program that "Sign In" button in your Navbar to open the login page, get the token from your Node.js engine, and unlock the "Reserve Now" button.

Are you ready to build the frontend Authentication system to finally let users log in?